properties.areaDesc: South Laramie Range Foothills; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 8 at 2:21AM MST until February 8 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
expected. Areas of blowing snow that could reduce visibilities
under a half mile at times.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County and
South Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...From 5 AM to 5 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Hazardous travel
conditions with blowoff and or blowover risks High to Extreme.
Areas of blowing and drifting snow likely to produce low
visibility and slick roads. Travel will be difficult
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
